## Broken Object Level Authorization (BOLA)

The most common API vulnerability. Occurs when an API exposes object IDs and doesn't verify the requester owns the resource.

```java
// VULNERABLE
@GetMapping("/orders/{orderId}")
public Order getOrder(@PathVariable Long orderId) {
    return orderRepo.findById(orderId).orElseThrow();
    // Any authenticated user can see ANY order by changing the ID!
}

// SECURE
@GetMapping("/orders/{orderId}")
public Order getOrder(@PathVariable Long orderId,
                      Authentication auth) {
    Order order = orderRepo.findById(orderId).orElseThrow();
    if (!order.getCustomerId().equals(auth.getName())) {
        throw new AccessDeniedException("Not your order");
    }
    return order;
}
```
